    <p>LONDON • Vet­eran Bri­tish golf com­men­ta­tor Peter Al­liss died at the age of 89 yes­ter­day. His fam­ily said his death was “un­ex­pected but peace­ful”.</p>
    <p>Known as “The voice of golf”, he had cov­ered the sport for the BBC for over half a cen­tury. Celebri­ties like John Cleese and Gary Lineker have paid trib­ute to “one of the great­est broad­cast­ers of his gen­er­a­tion”.</p>


